<TITLE> Gaddafi urges Swiss jihad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LIBYA, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)----- Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi urges jihad against Switzerland calling it an "infidel, obscene state." Jihad has been declared against Switzerland. But this time it's not coming from a radical mullah or militant group but a head of state, Libya's ever-controversial Muammar Gaddafi. He announced his anti-Swiss struggle, or Holy War, in front of a packed crowd and envoys from dozens of Muslim countries at a mosque in the eastern Libyan city of Benghazi. Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi said: "Any Muslim should boycott them. All Muslims should go to all the airports in the Muslim world and stop any Swiss plane from landing." Relations between Switzerland and Libya have been spiralling downward after Gaddafi's son was arrested in a Geneva hotel in 2008. Charges of domestic abuse were eventually dropped, but not before Libya had hit back at Switzerland by cutting oil supplies and withdrawing billions of dollars from Swiss banks. Two Swiss businessmen were also arrested and while one went free, the other is serving a four month sentence over a visa violation. Gaddafi also attacked a recent Swiss referendum that banned minarets in the country calling it an infidel state that was destroying mosques. But while the rhetoric seems to be escalating, the Swiss Foreign Ministry is being tight lipped in respo
